column1: # Design random-forest-leaf-neighbors in topology-specific Rosetta feature space
# Topology group index given in protein_groupings_by_uw.v1.metadata.csv: 4
# stabilityscore_cnn_calibrated: current best experimental stability score for each design
# stability_pred: prediction of rfr model trained on 4407 designs (on average)
# stability_diff: difference between experimental and predicted stability score
# num_nhbrs: average number of leaf-neighbors across all trees
# num_nhbrs_gt: average number of leaf-neighbors across all trees with stability score greater than the design
# num_nhbrs_lt: average number of leaf-neighbors across all trees with stability score less than the design
# diff: average difference between a design's stability and its leaf-neighbors' stabilities averaged across all trees
# gt_diff: average difference between a design's stability and those leaf-neighbors' whose stabilities are greater than the design's averaged across all trees
# lt_diff: average difference between a design's stability and those leaf-neighbors' whose stabilities are less than the design's averaged across all trees
# abs_diff: average absolute difference between a design's stability and its leaf-neighbors' stabilities averaged across all trees
# max_diff: maximum difference between a design's stability and its leaf-neighbors' stabilities averaged across all trees
# max_gt_diff: maximum difference between a design's stability and the leaf-neighbors' whose stabilities are greater than the design's averaged across all trees
# max_lt_diff: maximum difference between a design's stability and the leaf-neighbors' whose stabilities are less than the design's averaged across all trees
# max_abs_diff: maximum absolute difference between a design's stability and its leaf-neighbors' stabilities averaged across all trees
# leaf_nhbr_k: the design that is the kth most often a leaf-neighbor with its stability and the fraction of trees in which it is a neighbor
